// v1.3 (v2-updated): a non-strict lib whose silent-fallback shape
// requires strict contagion to surface. The previous fixture used
// `{ src: 1 + 2, val: { ...src } }` — v2 now flags that case
// cross-mode via `NonSpreadableSource` (no contagion needed), so
// the contagion test moved to a closure-param spread instead.
// Imported by `entry.relon`, which is strict — contagion makes the
// analyzer flag the inner `{ ...n }` whose source type is Any.
{ f: (n) => { ...n } }
